=== 票房 ===
電影於2009年5月7日晚上7時在美國正式上映，<ref>{{cite news|author=Peter Sciretta|title=Star Trek on May 7th|publisher=/Film|date=2009-04-13|url=http://www.slashfilm.com/2009/04/13/star-trek-on-may-7th/|accessdate=2009-04-13|archive-date=2010-01-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100115015328/http://www.slashfilm.com/2009/04/13/star-trek-on-may-7th/|dead-url=no}}</ref>公映當天便獲得400万美元的票房。在該周末，電影於美國本土票房收入累積到了79,204,289美元，其他國家的票房則共计3,550万美元。无论是否计算通脹因素，其票房都已击败了《[[星艦奇航記VIII：戰鬥巡航|星艦奇航記VIII：戰鬥巡航]]》，创下了《星空奇遇記》電影美国公映日最高票房的纪录。此外，电影还在[[IMAX|IMAX]]剧院赚取了850万美元，打破了《[[蝙蝠俠：黑夜之神|蝙蝠俠：黑夜之神]]》630万美元的紀錄。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://trekmovie.com/2009/05/11/final-numbers-in-star-trek-breaks-franchise-imax-records-outpeforming-batman-begins/|title=Final Numbers In - Star Trek Breaks Franchise & IMAX Records + Outpeforming Batman Begins|publisher=TrekMovie|date=2009-05-11|author=Rosario T. Calabria|accessdate=2009-05-12|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308014352/https://trekmovie.com/2009/05/11/final-numbers-in-star-trek-breaks-franchise-imax-records-outpeforming-batman-begins/|dead-url=no}}</ref>這齣電影是所有的星旅电影中本土總收入最高的一集，超越了其前辈《[[星际旅行IV：抢救未来|星际旅行IV：抢救未来]]》（總收入為109,713,132美元，未考虑通货膨胀因素）、《[[星际旅行：无限太空|星际旅行：无限太空]]》（考虑通货膨胀因素）。其上映首周末的收入约相当于《[[星际旅行V：终极先锋|终极先锋]]》、《[[星际旅行VI：未来之城|未来之城]]》、《[[星空奇遇記IX：星空反攻|星空反攻]]》及《[[星空奇遇記X：星戰啟示錄|星戰啟示錄]]》四部电影首映周末的總收入。<ref>{{cite web|title=Star Trek Movies|publisher=[[Box_Office_Mojo|Box Office Mojo]]|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/franchises/chart/?id=startrek.htm|accessdate=2009-06-17|archive-date=2012-02-14|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/65Rk8fn0U?url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/franchises/chart/?id=startrek.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>截至2009年8月23日，電影的本土票房收入為256,374,154美元，是2009年（迄今为止）美国票房收入第五高的電影。<ref name="boxofficemojo">{{cite web|title=Star Trek|publisher=[[Box_Office_Mojo|Box Office Mojo]]|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=startrek11.htm|accessdate=2009-08-24|archive-date=2010-12-12|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5uvcm6Wuw?url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=startrek11.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>电影在美國國外的总收入为126,385,382美元，全球总收入共382,759,536美元，低于《[[博物馆奇妙夜2|博物馆奇妙夜2]]》而位列第八。<ref name="boxofficemojo2">{{cite web|title=Star Trek|publisher=Box Office Mojo|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?view2=worldwide&yr=2009&p=.htm|accessdate=2009-07-20|archive-date=2012-06-28|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/68kO0r9hM?url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?view2=worldwide|dead-url=no}}</ref>尽管与其他电影相比，该片的美国国外票房只占到总票房收入的33%强，但派拉蒙依然对该片的国际发行感到满意，因为《星际旅行》系列从未在国外有过如此大的吸引力。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://trekmovie.com/2009/07/01/st09-tidbits-last-day-in-top-10-more-khan-debate-more-trekwars-more/|title=ST09 Tidbits: Last Day in Top 10? + More Khan Debate + More Trek/Wars + more|publisher=TrekMovie|date=2009-07-01|author=Anthony Pascale|accessdate=2009-08-02|archive-date=2021-03-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210307205002/https://trekmovie.com/2009/07/01/st09-tidbits-last-day-in-top-10-more-khan-debate-more-trekwars-more/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 反响 ===
截至2009年6月22日，这部电影在[[烂番茄|烂番茄]]网站上保持了95%的满意度，其中263篇评论中共有249篇给出了正面的评价，正面评价率达到了8.1/10，超过了这一系列此前的任何一部电影。<ref name="rottentomatoesreview">{{cite web|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/star_trek_11/|title=Rotten Tomatoes Review|accessdate=2009-06-02|archive-date=2015-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150130041636/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/star_trek_11/|dead-url=no}}</ref>在评论收集网站[[Metacritic|Metacritic]]上，《星际迷航》保持了83分的成绩，位列2009年迄今发行电影的并列第五名。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/star-trek|title=Metacritic Review of Star Trek|access-date=2010-09-21|archive-date=2018-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181023150041/https://www.metacritic.com/movie/star-trek|dead-url=no}}</ref>

《[[波士顿环球报|波士顿环球报]]》的泰·伯尔（{{small|Ty Burr}}）给此部电影评分4/4星，认为这部电影“令人极度满足”，<ref>原文：“ridiculously satisfying”．</ref>并称其为“迄今最为出色的前传”。<ref>原文：“best prequel ever”．</ref><ref name="bglobe">{{cite web|url=http://www.boston.com/ae/movies/articles/2009/05/05/a_fresh_frontier/|title=A Fresh Frontier|publisher=Boston Globe|accessdate=2009-05-06|date=2009-05-05|first=Ty|last=Burr|archive-date=2015-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150130041629/http://www.boston.com/ae/movies/articles/2009/05/05/a_fresh_frontier/|dead-url=no}}</ref>《[[娱乐周刊|娱乐周刊]]》的欧文·格莱伯曼（{{small|Owen Gleiberman}}）则给出了A-的评论，其中提到：“但《星际迷航》却是一个特例，这是那部异常长寿的科幻经典的一出巧妙而又不失感染力的外传，导演J·J·艾布拉姆斯精心构思了这一起源故事，避开了导致前作衰落的所有征兆”<ref>原文：“But in Star Trek, the clever and infectious reboot of the amazingly enduring sci-fi classic, director J.J. Abrams crafts an origin story that avoids any hint of the origin doldrums”．</ref>，并说到：“［……］拥有这样的船员，你何尝不能去拥抱未来。”<ref>原文：“[...] With a crew like this, you can welcome the future.</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Gleiberman |first=Owen |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20276708,00.html |title=Star Trek | Movie Review | Entertainment Weekly |publisher=Ew.com |date=2009-05-05 |accessdate=2009-05-10 |archive-date=2012-01-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120113024445/http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20276708,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>《{{link-en|完全电影|Total Film}}》的奥布里·戴（{{small|Aubrey Day}}）为此部电影评分4/5星，她说：“轻快、健实以及对美好未来的许诺，这是几十年来最清爽的星旅作品。”<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.totalfilm.com/reviews/cinema/star-trek-1|title=Star Trek Review, Total Film|publisher=totalfilm.com|quote=Buoyant, buffed and with the promise of even better to come, this is the freshest Trek in decades.|accessdate=2009-06-02|archive-date=2014-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140709163314/http://www.totalfilm.com/reviews/cinema/star-trek-1|dead-url=no}}</ref>《[[SFX_(杂志)|SFX]]》杂志的伊恩·贝里曼（{{small|Ian Berriman}}）给出了5/5的分数，对该系列的艾布拉姆斯版本大加赞誉，说到：“这个夏天，随着艾布拉姆斯迅猛的史诗作品让所有反对者绞尽脑汁后，在后花园和公园中将响起小男孩们模仿相位枪开火的声音，他们正在玩柯克和斯波克的游戏呢。”<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sfx.co.uk/page/sfx?entry=film_review_star_trek|title=Star Trek Review, SFX|publisher=sfx.co.uk|quote=This summer, after Abrams’s explosive epic has nerve-pinched all the opposition, back gardens and parks will ring with the sound of young boys zapping imaginary phasers as they play Kirk and Spock.|accessdate=2009-06-02|archive-date=2009-04-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090411111331/http://www.sfx.co.uk/page/sfx?entry=film_review_star_trek|dead-url=no}}</ref>《[[帝国_(杂志)|帝国]]》杂志的科林·肯尼迪（{{small|Colin Kennedy}}）给出了4/5星的分数，评论说：“在整部系列中，进取号第一次踏上了真正激动人心的旅程”；<ref>原文：“for the first time in the franchise, the Enterprise is a genuine thrill-ride”．</ref>然而，文中亦提到：“和它生机勃勃的年轻演员一样，这部星旅电影不乏动作、情感、性感与活力，但却缺乏理智。”<ref>{{cite news | title = Empire Magazine Star Trek (2009) Review | url = http://www.empireonline.com/reviews/reviewcomplete.asp?FID=134061 | publisher = [[帝国_(杂志)|帝国]] | author = Colin Kennedy | accessdate = 2009-06-02 | archive-date = 2015-09-24 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150924134132/http://www.empireonline.com/reviews/reviewcomplete.asp?FID=134061 | dead-url = no }}</ref>

{{link-en|黑暗地平线 (网站)|Dark Horizons|黑暗地平线}}网站的对制片人们面临的任务发表了意见，说到：“艾布拉姆斯和他的团队是如何让这一系列乃至‘[[太空歌剧|太空歌剧]]’流派迅速重振并更苏的？要把这点解释清楚，绝不是三言两语能办到的。”<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.darkhorizons.com/reviews/911/Star-Trek/ | title=Star Trek - April 13th 2009 | publisher=Dark Horizons | accessdate=2009-04-16 | date=2009-04-13 | last=Franklin | first=Garth | quote=It simply can not be stated enough how effectively Abrams and his crew have revived and repositioned not just the franchise but the 'space opera' genre itself. | archive-date=2016-03-09 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160309154555/http://www.darkhorizons.com/reviews/911/star-trek | dead-url=no }}</ref>《[[好莱坞报道|好莱坞报道]]》的雷·贝内特（{{small|Ray Bennett}}）说到：“J·J·艾布拉姆斯让进取号星舰拥有了一切，乃至绰绰有余了……进入曲速时的壮观画面被表现得淋漓尽致，它的演员是如此专业，所有相似的角色即刻便能被区分开来，这部电影为派拉蒙电影公司延续了这一系列的生命。”<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/film-reviews/film-review-star-trek-1003964428.story |title=Star Trek film review |publisher=好莱坞报道 |date=2009-04-20 |accessdate=2009-05-10 |quote=J.J. Abrams gives the Starship Enterprise all its got, and it's more than enough... Paced at warp speed with spectacular action sequences rendered brilliantly and with a cast so expert that all the familiar characters are instantly identifiable, the film gives Paramount Pictures a new lease of life on its franchise. |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090423024101/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/film-reviews/film-review-star-trek-1003964428.story |archivedate=2009-04-23 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>《[[每日邮报|每日邮报]]》的克里斯·图基（{{small|Chris Tookey}}）给电影打出了5/5星的成绩，并评论说：“其结果是，这部电影不仅成为了11部《星际旅行》电影中最上乘之作，它还必将进入历史上最出众的前传之列。”<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/reviews/article-1172164/Out-world-The-Mails-film-critic-gives-verdict-new-Star-Trek-movie.html|title=Out of this world! The Mail's film critic gives his verdict on the new Star Trek movie|format=mdy|accessdate=April 22, 2009|quote=The result is not only by far the best of the 11 Star Trek movies, it must rank as the outstanding prequel of all time.|archive-date=2021-03-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210323012142/https://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/reviews/article-1172164/Out-world-The-Mails-film-critic-gives-verdict-new-Star-Trek-movie.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>《[[卫报|卫报]]》评说到：“有了阳光的年轻演员以及轻松愉快的气氛，这出《星际旅行》的外传有几分像太空中的《[[90210|90210]]》，但在克里斯·派恩饰演的柯克舰长下，这一系列总算找到了块纯金打造的明星。”<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/filmblog/2009/apr/21/star-trek|title=JJ Abrams's Star Trek: we have liftoff|format=mdy|accessdate=2009-06-02|quote=With its shiny young cast and breezy tone, the rebooted Star Trek is a bit like 90210 set in space, but in Chris Pine's Captain Kirk, the franchise has found a solid gold star.|archive-date=2013-05-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130520220053/http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/filmblog/2009/apr/21/star-trek|dead-url=no}}</ref>《[[世界新闻报|世界新闻报]]》的罗比·科林（{{small|Robbie Collin}}）给出了5/5星的成绩，并说它是“最出色的科幻作品。”<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.newsoftheworld.co.uk/entertainment/film/285730/Star-Trek-12A-Film-is-overseen-by-Lost-creator-JJ-Abram-Stars-Eric-Bana-Chris-Pine-and-Zachary-Quinto.html| title = Star Trek review - Verdict: Vulcan Brilliant| format = mdy| accessdate = 2009-05-03| quote = science fiction at its finest.| archive-date = 2009-06-24| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090624161426/http://www.newsoftheworld.co.uk/entertainment/film/285730/Star-Trek-12A-Film-is-overseen-by-Lost-creator-JJ-Abram-Stars-Eric-Bana-Chris-Pine-and-Zachary-Quinto.html| dead-url = no}}</ref>《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》的曼诺拉·达吉斯（{{small|Manohla Dargis}}）称此电影是“从最新设想的往昔吹来的一阵清新、明快的风”<ref>原文：“A bright, shiny blast from a newly imagined past”．</ref>，且是“电视节目拥有称谓神话创作者能力的明证。”<ref>原文：“A testament to television’s power as mythmaker.”</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Dargis |first=Manohla |url=http://movies.nytimes.com/2009/05/08/movies/08trek.html |title=Movie Review - Star Trek - A Franchise Goes Boldly Backward - NYTimes.com |publisher=Movies.nytimes.com |date= |accessdate=2009-05-10 |archive-date=2012-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120222154018/http://movies.nytimes.com/2009/05/08/movies/08trek.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>《暂停》周刊悉尼版（{{small|''Time Out Sydney''}}）的格雷戈里·穆尔（{{small|Gregory Moore}}）给出了5/6星，并总结说：“它不只是一部伟大的《星际旅行》电影：它还为伟大的电影画上了句点。”<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.timeoutsydney.com.au/film/event/star-trek.aspx|title=Star Trek Review, Time Out Sydney|quote=It isn't just a great Star Trek movie: it's a great movie full stop.|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090428072556/http://www.timeoutsydney.com.au/film/event/star-trek.aspx|archivedate=2009-04-28}}</ref>《{{link-en|页岩 (杂志)|Slate (magazine)|页岩}}》杂志的达娜·史蒂文斯（{{small|Dana Stevens}}）对电影给出了正面的评价：“［……］《星际旅行》既不是系列也不是财产，它是一个世界。艾布拉姆斯精心构建的前传表现了这一世界的（大部分）规则，而更重要的是，它保留了初-{}-代《星际旅行》的乐观、好奇和幽默的精神。”<ref>{{cite web |last=Stevens |first=Dana |url=http://www.slate.com/id/2217854/ |title=Star Trek reviewed. - By Dana Stevens - Slate Magazine |publisher=Slate.com |date=2009-05-06 |accessdate=2009-05-10 |quote=[...] Star Trek is neither a franchise nor a property. It's a world. Abrams' cannily constructed prequel respects (for the most part) the rules of that world and, more importantly, retains the original Star Trek's spirit of optimism, curiosity, and humor. |archive-date=2011-01-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110115084145/http://www.slate.com/id/2217854/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>《[[滚石_(杂志)|滚石]]》杂志给出了3.5/4星的成绩，提到：“同《星际迷航》一起，夏日已正式进入了曲速状态，这一出向经典1960年代电视剧致敬的令人兴奋的电影，依然在勇敢地航向前人——包括威廉·夏特纳和伦纳德·尼莫伊在内——所未至的领域。［……］这是一份不可拒绝的快乐请柬，你还能对夏日的电影有什么苛求？”<ref>{{cite web |author=(Posted: May 6, 2009) |url=http://www.rollingstone.com/reviews/movie/20314046/review/27993027/star_trek |title=Star Trek : Review |publisher=Rolling Stone |date=2009-05-06 |accessdate=2009-06-02 |quote=Summer officially hits warp speed with Star Trek, a burst of pure filmmaking exhilaration that manages to pay homage to the classic 1960s TV series and still boldly go where no man, William Shatner and Leonard Nimoy included, has gone before. [...] It's an irresistible invitation for fun. What more can you ask of a summer movie? |archive-date=2009-05-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090510081300/http://www.rollingstone.com/reviews/movie/20314046/review/27993027/star_trek |dead-url=yes }}</ref>《[[时代_(杂志)|时代]]》杂志的玛丽·波尔斯（{{small|Mary Pols}}）说到：“这是一部真正的家庭片，暴力成分相对较少，好笑亦不过度粗鲁；甚至还有不少感人的时刻。”<ref>{{cite news |last=Pols |first=Mary |url=http://www.time.com/time/arts/article/0,8599,1896513,00.html |title=The New Star Trek Movie: It Will Leave Fans Beaming |publisher=TIME |date=2009-05-06 |accessdate=2009-06-02 |quote=It's a real family film, relatively light on the violence and funny without being overly crude; it even has some touching moments. |archive-date=2013-08-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130826151858/http://www.time.com/time/arts/article/0,8599,1896513,00.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

《[[洛杉矶时报|洛杉矶时报]]》的评论员肯尼思·图兰（{{small|Kenneth Turan}}）说到：“［……］我很乐意地报告说，尽管这不是一部完美的电影，但重塑《星际旅行》的成功已足以让每一个人长舒一口气了。尽管这部电影看上去像是摄入了过多的咖啡因，尽管它还有一些不合理，但这部《星际迷航》已经迅速、有意地在新舊影迷間的鸿沟上架出了一座桥梁。”<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2009/may/07/entertainment/et-trek7|title='Star Trek' takes the universe by storm|publisher=洛杉矶时报|author=Kenneth Turan|date=2009-05-07|accessdate=2009-06-02|quote=[...] it is pleasant to report that though it's not perfect, the reconstituted "Star Trek" is successful enough for everyone to breathe a sigh of relief. Though it has its over-caffeinated aspects and its missteps, this "Star Trek" has in general bridged the gap between the old and the new with alacrity and purpose.|archive-date=2018-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181101142139/http://articles.latimes.com/2009/may/07/entertainment/et-trek7|dead-url=no}}</ref>《[[视听俱乐部|视听俱乐部]]》的基思·菲普斯（{{small|Keith Phipps}}）给出了B+的分数，并从整个系列的角度对电影的特效进行了评价：“那些历史悠久的《星际旅行》电视剧并没有多少存货够得上新电影拿出来重用、破坏、现代化或者挨轰。”<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.avclub.com/articles/star-trek,27714|title=Star Trek|publisher=视听俱乐部|quote=the venerable Star Trek series hasn’t so much been pulled out of storage with this new film as dusted off, broken down to its most basic parts, streamlined, and sent blazing off at an acute angle from its original course.|date=2009-05-07|accessdate=2009-06-02|archive-date=2012-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120103083050/http://www.avclub.com/articles/star-trek,27714/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

还有一些影评人给出了较少的正面评价，其中包括[[罗杰·埃伯特|罗杰·埃伯特]]，他只给了2.5/4星的分数，说到：“在吉恩·罗登伯里的时代，节目的故事都是带有科学问题、理想或哲学价值的；而现在却被缩减成了吵闹见血的动作片。”<ref>原文：“The Gene Roddenberry years, when stories might play with questions of science, ideals or philosophy, have been replaced by stories reduced to loud and colorful action.”</ref>不过，他依然抱有希望地说到：“也许下一部电影会让这些角色面临更复杂更曲折的挑战。”<ref>原文：“Perhaps the next one will engage these characters in a more challenging and devious story.”</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://rogerebert.suntimes.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20090506/REVIEWS/905069997 |title=Star Trek :: rogerebert.com :: Reviews |publisher=Rogerebert.suntimes.com |date=2009-05-06 |accessdate=2009-05-10 |archive-date=2009-05-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090509142939/http://rogerebert.suntimes.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=%2F20090506%2FREVIEWS%2F905069997 |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[IGN|IGN英国]]的奥兰多·帕菲特（{{small|Orlando Parfitt}}）给出了3.5/5分，提到：“作为一部动作片，它并不成功，或者毫无意义”，他说他困惑于尼禄的目的，并且难于理解“迷宫般”（{{small|labyrinthine}}）的剧情。这名评论员还提到，他“从未有过似乎柯克或斯波克真正遇到危险的那种感觉。”<ref>{{cite news|url=http://uk.movies.ign.com/articles/973/973956p2.html|title=Star Trek Review, IGN UK|quote=never felt as though Kirk or Spock were in genuine peril.|accessdate=2009-06-02|archive-date=2010-06-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100618071653/http://uk.movies.ign.com/articles/973/973956p2.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>《[[赫芬顿邮报|赫芬顿邮报]]》的斯科特·门德尔松（{{small|Scott Mendelson}}）给电影评分2.5/4，说到：“这是部给那些从未看过电视剧或电影的人们看的《星际旅行》，角色的刻画并不精细，而对哲理的解释也太过直白。”<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/scott-mendelson/huff-post-review---star-t_b_200098.html|title=HuffPost Review -- Star Trek (2009)|quote=this film is Star Trek for people who have never seen the shows or the movies, and furthermore need their characters drawn in broad strokes and the philosophies explicitly explained in monologue.|author=Scott Mendelson|date=2009-05-08|accessdate=2009-06-04|publisher=[[赫芬顿邮报|赫芬顿邮报]]|archive-date=2017-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170707173027/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/scott-mendelson/huff-post-review---star-t_b_200098.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

